Shell WebUI controller for Phase 11 settings surface.

chrome://slayzone-settings/ is a client-side-routed multi-tab shell that
ports packages/domains/settings/src/client/UserSettingsDialog.tsx to a
chrome:// WebUI. Tabs: Appearance / Worktrees / Providers / Panels /
Data / Backup / Labs / MCP / Diagnostics / Telemetry / About — the 11
tabs actually shipped by UserSettingsDialog, not the 5 aspirational tabs
named in the Phase 11 task card. Documented on C5 as parity deviation
webui:settings:taxonomy-from-dialog.

The controller is shell-only: no SlayzoneSettingsHost and no dedicated
settings.mojom. Tab navigation + URL-hash routing + keyboard cycling
are entirely client-side React; per-tab hosts land in 11.2–11.5 when
each tab's data contract becomes concrete. Tracked as C5 deviation
webui:settings:host-deferred. This keeps the shell decoupled from the
468-handler sidecar ledger so parity verification for the nav surface
doesn't gate on tab-specific wiring.

Reuses slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource (patch 0021) with a settings-
specific missing-bundle HTML. No SlayzoneBrowserView edits — settings
is a modal surface hosted by Phase 10's dialog/Widget infrastructure,
so there is no per-BrowserView slot identity to plumb through.

Collateral note: kChromeUISlayzoneSettingsHost / kChromeUISlayzoneSettingsURL
constants + the BUILD.gn / webui_registry.cc entries landed ahead of
this commit as part of Phase 10.1 (dba90e0d77ab6) due to parallel-
agent in-tree scheduling. This patch adds only the missing
slayzone_settings_ui.{cc,h} pair that those references resolve to.

Outer-repo bundle ships in packages/webui/settings/ alongside this
commit.
